explanation.en:
The radial nerve {{exhibit_2}} is the largest branch of the brachial plexus and receives fibers from C5-T1. It innervates all the EXTENSOR MUSCLES of the upper limb below the shoulder and provides sensory innervation to the skin of the posterior arm, forearm, and dorsal lateral hand.

This nerve tracks within the radial groove on the humerus; therefore, it is VULNERABLE to traumatic injury at the humeral midshaft. The nerve can also be injured (eg, penetrating stab wound) during its superficial course within the axilla. Patients with proximal radial neuropathy typically have weakness during wrist and finger extension (wrist drop) and variable sensory loss over the posterior arm and forearm.

(Choices A, B, D, and E) Damage to the median or ulnar nerve can result in weakness on wrist flexion. Damage to the median nerve can also result in weakness on thumb opposition, whereas ulnar nerve damage may limit finger abduction and thumb adduction. {{exhibit_3}} {{exhibit_4}} {{exhibit_5}} {{exhibit_6}}

explanation.zh:
桡神经{{exhibit_2}}是臂丛最大的分支，接收来自C5-T1的纤维。它支配肩部以下上肢的所有伸肌，并为上臂、前臂和手背外侧的皮肤提供感觉神经支配。

该神经在肱骨上的桡神经沟内走行；因此，它易受肱骨中段的创伤性损伤。该神经也可能在其腋窝内的浅表走行过程中受到损伤（例如，穿透性刺伤）。近端桡神经病变的患者通常在腕关节和手指伸展时出现无力（腕下垂），以及上臂和前臂后部不同程度的感觉丧失。

（选项A、B、D和E）正中神经或尺神经损伤可导致腕关节屈曲无力。正中神经损伤也可导致拇指对掌无力，而尺神经损伤可能会限制手指外展和拇指内收。{{exhibit_3}} {{exhibit_4}} {{exhibit_5}} {{exhibit_6}}
